LOCALE_ALERT_MESSAGE_GROUPTIP:
By assigning users to groups, you can make managing and classifying users much simpler. Once a user has been assigned to a group, all permissions associated with the group are assigned to the user automatically. Any changes made to the group, are also made to the user. This also works in the opposite direction, if a user is assigned to multiple groups, the user will be assigned the permissions from all the groups the user is associated with. This makes managing multiple users permissions very easy.
You can manage users by following these steps:
1) Create a group
2) Add a user to the group
3) Assign a role to the group

LOCAL_INTELLIGENT_DIAGNOSIS_MAINTENANCE_: It is recommended to continuously pay attention to the trend of partial discharge signal, and conduct on-site retest to confirm and judge the source of abnormal signal in combination with the opportunity to enter the station. After confirmation according to the diagnostic test, it is recommended to shorten the test cycle, monitor four times a day, focus on the signal change trend, and carry out maintenance when there is an opportunity

It is suggested to focus on the development trend of partial discharge signal, and timely arrange the station to conduct on-site retest to confirm and judge the location and severity of abnormal signal. Partial discharge will corrode insulating materials, further develop into branches, and finally lead to insulation breakdown. The development of insulation defects is accelerated and irreversible. After detection and confirmation, it is recommended to arrange power outage maintenance as soon as possible to eliminate potential defects, shorten the monitoring interval before power outage maintenance, adjust it to 1 hour for monitoring, and install intensive care online monitoring if necessary.
